g?fit=526%2C349&amp;ssl=1" data-large-file="https://i1.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/image4-1.jpeg?fit=1080%2C715&amp;ssl=1" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-431067" src="https://i1.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/image4-1.jpeg?ssl=1" alt="" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/image4-1.jpeg?w=1080&amp;ssl=1 1080w, https://i1.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/image4-1.jpeg?resize=526%2C349&amp;ssl=1 526w, https://i1.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/image4-1.jpeg?resize=768%2C508&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i1.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/image4-1.jpeg?resize=750%2C497&amp;ssl=1 750w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> He further stated that the company would continue to invest huge resources to expand its businesses and help create more job opportunities for Nigerians. Speaking at the ceremony, the Executive Governor of Ogun State, Prince Dapo Abiodun commended the efforts of Nigerian Breweries Plc in committing huge resources to the expansion of production lines in the factory. <img data-attachment-id="431065" data-permalink="https://www.premiumtimesng.com/promoted/431061-nigerian-breweries-commissions-n5-1-billion-ultra-modern-automated-pet-bottling-line-in-ijebu-ode.html/attachment/image2-42" data-orig-file="https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/image2-1.jpeg?fit=1080%2C715&amp;ssl=1" data-orig-size="1080,715" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="image2" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/image2-1.jpeg?fit=526%2C349&amp;ssl=1" data-large-file="https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/image2-1.jpeg?fit=1080%2C715&amp;ssl=1" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-431065" src="https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/image2-1.jpeg?ssl=1" alt="" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/image2-1.jpeg?w=1080&amp;ssl=1 1080w, https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/image2-1.jpeg?resize=526%2C349&amp;ssl=1 526w, https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/image2-1.jpeg?resize=768%2C508&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/image2-1.jpeg?resize=750%2C497&amp;ssl=1 750w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> “As you are aware, Nigerian Breweries Plc remains one of the largest taxpayers because two of their major plants are located in Ogun state; one in Ijebu-Ode and another in Ota.” “This is indeed a welcome development for the people of Ogun state given the economic potentials attached to this investment. For us, we are quite confident that this investment would, no doubt, assist in enhancing economic prosperity not only for the community but Ogun state as a whole,” the governor stated. <img data-attachment-id="431064" data-permalink="https://www.premiumtimesng.com/promoted/431061-nigerian-breweries-commissions-n5-1-billion-ultra-modern-automated-pet-bottling-line-in-ijebu-ode.html/attachment/image1-1-22" data-orig-file="https://i2.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/image1-1-1.jpeg?fit=1080%2C715&amp;ssl=1" data-orig-size="1080,715" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;Picasa&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quo